# Cloudflare Pages redirects — OPTIONAL same-origin API proxy.
#
# Rename this file to `_redirects` (no extension) to proxy API calls through the
# Pages domain instead of calling the tunnel cross-origin. With this in place,
# leave VITE_API_BASE_URL unset so the app uses the default "/api" base — every
# request stays same-origin and NO CORS configuration is needed on the backend.
#
# Replace the destination with your Cloudflare Tunnel hostname.
# The 200 status makes it a transparent proxy (rewrite), not a 30x redirect, so
# the Authorization header and request method are preserved.

/api/*  https://api.example.com/:splat  200

# SPA fallback — serve index.html for client-side routes (keep this LAST).
/*      /index.html                     200
